    {
        "content": "<p>Generally speaking, <code>grind</code> attributes for <code>instance</code>s essentially do nothing.<br>\nYou should remove <code>grind</code> attributes from instances and make new <code>grind</code> lemmas, and change <code>grind only</code> into <code>grind</code>.</p>",
        "id": 567243574,
        "sender_full_name": "Miyahara Kō",
        "timestamp": 1767985174
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"569722\">@Miyahara Kō</span> what kind of <code>grind</code> lemmas should be implemented? I've had similar situations where I was expecting <code>grind</code> to just understand what a given notation (implemented on type classes) unfolds to, and ended up adding explicit lemmas just for unfolding the notation. But that felt a bit strange as other tactics like <code>simp</code> don't require such lemmas.</p>",
